org.jamsim.r
Class RInterfaceHL

java.lang.Object
  org.jamsim.r.RInterfaceHL

public final class RInterfaceHL
extends Object

General purpose interface to the R high level engine. Provides

  • Single instance, because R is single threaded.
  • Assignment of R objects.
  • Parsing and evaluation of commands in R in multiple ways ( eval(String), parseEvalPrint(String), parseEvalTry(String)).
  • Message output to the R console.
Uses the org.rosuda.REngine interface, which prevents re-entrance and has Java side objects that represent R data structures, rather than the lower level org.rosuda.JRI interface which doesn't have these features.

eval

public org.rosuda.REngine.REXP eval(String expr)
                             throws RInterfaceException
Evaluate an expression in R in the global environment. Does not explicitly call "parse" so any syntax errors will result in the unhelpful "parse error" exception message. Any evaluation errors will have the error messages printed to the console and return the exception message "error during evaluation". Unlike, the REPL and parseEvalPrint(String), does not print the result of the expression (ie: does just the E part of the REPL). Any prints within the expression or functions called by the expression will print. Warnings produced by the expression will not be printed.

Parameters:
expr - expression to evaluate.
Returns:
REXP result of the evaluation. Not printed to the console.
Throws:
RInterfaceException - if problem during parse or evaluation. Parse errors will simply return the message "parse error". Any evaluation errors with have the error messages printed to the console and return the exception message "error during evaluation".

parseEvalTry

public org.rosuda.REngine.REXP parseEvalTry(String expr)
                                     throws RInterfaceException
Wraps a parse and try around an eval. The parse will generate syntax error messages, and the try will catch parse and evaluation errors and return them in the exception as opposed to printing it on the console.

Parameters:
expr - expression to try and parse and eval
Returns:
REXP result of the evaluation.
Throws:
RInterfaceException - if there is a parse or evaluation error the error message is returned in the exception. Nothing printed to the console.

parseEvalPrint

public org.rosuda.REngine.REXP parseEvalPrint(String expr)
Wraps a parse around an eval and prints (shows) result. Returns the expression result AND prints it to the console if it is visible, ie: the REP parts of the REPL. Errors & warnings are are output to the console, ie: doesn't produce Java exceptions for expression errors. Uses R global environment.

Parameters:
expr - expression to parse, eval and show
Returns:
REXP result of the evaluation. Also printed to the console if visible. Returns null if there was an exception generated whilst evaluating the expression.
